<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B69165878E8FE20262CFD19" pageId="25" pageNumber="130" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B69165878E8FE20262CFD19" blockId="25.[136,1452,374,1157]" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B69165878E8FE2026CBFE55" bold="true" box="[189,401,482,508]" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B69165879F8FE212511FE55" authorityName="R. E. Fries" authorityYear="1908" box="[429,587,482,509]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="25" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B69165879F8FE212511FE55" box="[429,587,482,509]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">S. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
var. 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B6916587AD3FE202438FE55" box="[646,866,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">pseudo-rhombifolia</emphasis>
belongs to section 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B6916587C14FE202325FE55" box="[1089,1151,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="25" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Sidae">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B6916587C14FE202325FE55" box="[1089,1151,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">Sidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation id="4A6403360B6916587CC5FE2023BEFE55" box="[1168,1252,482,508]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,340,364]" captionTargetBox="[144,1440,425,1289]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Sections of Sida with species occurring in Rio Grande do Sul state, and their diagnostic features, according to Fryxell (1985) and Krapovickas (2003)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39" pageId="25" pageNumber="130" tableUuid="539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39">Table 1</tableCitation>
) and is a species morphologically related to 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B6916587997FDC42517FD89" box="[450,589,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="25" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viarum">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B6916587997FDC42517FD89" box="[450,589,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">Sida viarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B6916587ADFFDC42410FD89" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[650,842,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="25" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhombifolia">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B6916587ADFFDC42410FD89" box="[650,842,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">Sida rhombifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B6916587B0EFDC4236AFD89" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[859,1072,518,544]" pageId="25" pageNumber="130" pagination="65 - 118" refId="ref19583" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2014) Nuevas especies de Sida Seccion Sida (Malvaceae). Bonplandia 23: 65 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 232258" type="journal article" year="2014">Krapovickas 2014</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B6916587C6BFDC4226BFD89" author="Monteiro-Filho, H. da" box="[1086,1329,518,544]" pageId="25" pageNumber="130" pagination="501 - 522" refId="ref20015" refString="Monteiro-Filho, H. da C. (1949) As especies argentinas, brasileiras e uruguayas da seccao Malvinda do genero Sida (Malvaceas). Lilloa 17: 501 - 522." type="journal article" year="1949">Monteiro-Filho 1949</bibRefCitation>
). It differs from these species by the presence of 6–8 mericarps (rarely nine), vs. 5 mericarps in 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B6916587C7EFDE923CFFDED" box="[1067,1173,555,581]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="25" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viarum">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B6916587C7EFDE923CFFDED" box="[1067,1173,555,581]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">S. viarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 9–14 mericarps in 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B6916587DC3FDE92656FDC1" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="25" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhombifolia">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B6916587DC3FDE92656FDC1" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">S. rhombifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; presence of simple trichomes on the margins of the calyx lobes; flowers solitary or crowded in subsessile axillary glomerules, the pedicels up to 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B6916587A19FDB025C4FD24" box="[588,670,626,653]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="25" pageNumber="130" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
long on solitary flowers (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B6916587B99FDB02327FD25" box="[972,1149,626,652]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="22.[136,229,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,190,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[177,1411,190,1932]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 11. A–D. Sida rubifolia. A. Flower. B. Adaxial surface of leaf. C. Prostrate habit. D. Calyx and corolla. E–K. Sida spinosa. E. Flower. F. Abaxial surface of leaf. G. Adaxial surface of leaf. H. Habit. I. Mature schizocarp. J. Branch with tubercle at petiole base. K. Branch. L–Q. Sida tuberculata. L. Branch with leaves, mature and immature schizocarps. M. Adaxial surface of leaf. N. Abaxial surface of leaf. O. Mature schizocarps. P. Branch with flower. Q. Habit. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415511/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">Figures 11L–Q</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B6916587CDEFDB023E0FD25" box="[1163,1210,626,652]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[136,229,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-54@26.[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Mericarps. A. Sida anomala. B. Sida confusa. C. Sida farroupilhensis. D. Sida glaziovii. E. Sida cerradoensis. F. Sida cordifolia. G. Sida dubia. H. Sida linifolia. I. Sida lonchitis. J. Sida nemorensis. K. Sida paradoxa. L. Sida planicaulis. M. Sida potentilloides.N. Sida reitzii. O. Sida regnellii. P. Sida rhombifolia.Q. Sida riedelii. R. Sida rubifolia.S. Sida spinosa.T. Sida tuberculata. U. Sida urens. V. Sida viarum. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415519/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">14T</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B6916587C86FDB022FDFD24" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[1235,1447,626,653]" pageId="25" pageNumber="130" pagination="292 - 333" refId="ref19401" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2005) Malvaceae. In: Bacigalupo, N. M. (Ed.) Flora Ilustrada de Entre-Rios. 6 (4 b). Colecc. Ci. Inst. Nac. Tecnol. Agropecu, pp. 292 - 333." type="book chapter" year="2005">Krapovickas 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B69165878DDFD542630FD19" author="Brandao, J. L. &amp; Baracho, G. S. &amp; De Sales, M. F. &amp; Filho, M. P. V." box="[136,362,662,688]" pageId="25" pageNumber="130" pagination="205 - 227" refId="ref18144" refString="Brandao, J. L., Baracho, G. S., De Sales, M. F. &amp; Filho, M. P. V. (2017) Synopsis of Sida (Malvaceae, Malvoideae, Malveae) in the state of Pernambuco, Brazil. Phytotaxa 307 (3): 205 - 227. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 307.3.5" type="journal article" year="2017">
Brandão 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B69165878BBFD55267CFD19" box="[238,294,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B69165878E8FD7826B3FC21" pageId="25" pageNumber="130" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B69165878E8FD7826B3FC21" blockId="25.[136,1452,374,1157]" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B69165878E8FD78258DFD7D" bold="true" box="[189,727,698,724]" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">Distribution, habitat and conservation status:</emphasis>
—The species occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B6916587BB0FD782301FD7D" box="[997,1115,698,724]" name="Venezuela" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B6916587C31FD7823E3FD7D" box="[1124,1209,698,724]" name="Bolivia" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B6916587C96FD792276FD7C" box="[1219,1324,699,725]" name="Paraguay" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B6916587D60FD7822FDFD7D" box="[1333,1447,698,724]" name="Argentina" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B69165878DDFD1D27B0FD50" box="[136,234,735,761]" name="Uruguay" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B691658794AFD1C2639FD51" box="[287,355,734,760]" name="Brazil" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(northeast, midwest, southeast and south) (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B6916587B16FD1C234EFD51" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[835,1044,734,760]" pageId="25" pageNumber="130" pagination="65 - 118" refId="ref19583" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2014) Nuevas especies de Sida Seccion Sida (Malvaceae). Bonplandia 23: 65 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 232258" type="journal article" year="2014">Krapovickas 2014</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B6916587C4BFD1C23F4FD51" author="Bovini, M. G." box="[1054,1198,734,760]" pageId="25" pageNumber="130" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B6916587C88FD1C22F1FD51" box="[1245,1451,734,760]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
the species occurs in Park grassland, Sandy grassland, Shallow soil grassland, Inland sub-montane grassland, Bush grassland, Highland grassland, 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B69165879BAFCE42513FCE9" box="[495,585,806,832]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Aristida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Aristida</taxonomicName>
grassland, Coastal grassland and Inland subtropical Forest (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B6916587D56FCE42232FCE9" box="[1283,1384,806,832]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="17.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[267,1344,252,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-17@17.[205,1383,190,1929]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 8. Distribution map of Sida riedelii, S. ramoniana, S. regnellii, S. reitzii and S. tuberculata in Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415505/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="130">Figure 8</figureCitation>
). The species is here considered Least Concern (LC) because it has large EOO and AOO, since it is a frequent and ruderal species, and widely distributed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
